{"actual_usd":0.124345,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":195,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24284,"reply":"\"No... not the way I'd say it.\" *I rub a thumb along a faint ridge of dried clay on my apron, watching the light shift across the table a moment before I look back at you.* \"The cross is not just pain. It's where Christ actually gave himself for us—where sin was borne, where the cost was paid. The resurrection matters because it shows death did not keep him, that his sacrifice truly holds, that what he did on the cross wasn't swallowed up and lost.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, the bench giving a soft creak.* \"If you split them too hard, you end up thinning both. The cross without the resurrection becomes tragedy. The resurrection without the cross becomes victory with no wound in it. Scripture keeps them together—Christ died for our sins, and he was raised.\" \"Which part are you pressing on—the 'atonement' word, or the fear that people make too little of the resurrection?\"","rolling_24h_usd":47.31200500000003,"run_id":"f0af14b2-3a21-494b-aea8-842267d0ded6"}
